For some time I used a Radio Shack 30-amp Auto Relay, Radio Shack 
#275-226.  This I connected to the wiring harness using several short 
"pigtails" so as to not damage the original wiring.  I am glad I did so 
because I subsequently came across a stock relay in a bone yard.
